-- J&J to recall gas relief dye free drops
-- 
-- Mon Nov 10, 2008 3:36pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/11/10/us-jandj-recall-idUSTRE4A975820081110

 

 (Reuters) - Johnson & Johnson Merck Consumer Pharmaceuticals Company announced on Monday an urgent voluntary nationwide recall of infants' Mylicon (R) gas relief dye free drops (simethicone-antigas) non-staining due to possible metal fragments. 

 Other highlights: * Says JJMCP voluntarily recalling about 12,000 units of infants' mylicon gas relief dye free drops * Says some bottles could include metal fragments that were generated during manufacturing process (Bangalore Equities Newsroom)